# Analysis engine (frozen)

`analysis-engine.ts`, `synthetic-data-generator.ts`, and
`analysis-engine.test.ts` are complete and verified. Treat them as frozen.

- Do not change the statistics: robust median/MAD baselines, personal z-scores,
  prior-outcome-controlled regression, moving-block bootstrap CIs, and
  Benjamini-Hochberg correction on BOTH the confirmatory hypothesis family AND
  the case-control precursor signals.
- The acceptance gate: on `noiseOnly()` data the engine must surface ZERO
  confirmatory findings after BH. Keep `analysis-engine.test.ts` green.
- Confirmatory analysis uses the pre-registered hypothesis set only. The
  exploratory grid is firewalled: raw stats, no insights, no BH labels.
- `recurring_pattern` = a surfaced finding. `possible_association` = a
  "watching" tier that is NEVER promoted into the insight feed.
- The generator and test are server/dev tooling only (the generator imports
  `node:fs`). Never import them into client components.
- Consume engine output through `analyze()`. Do not reimplement any analysis
  inside React components.
- If a new relationship needs testing, add it to the pre-registered hypotheses
  with a direction and lag — do not bolt ad-hoc correlations onto the UI.
